field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Jazz5 is Ir on Ti on Au. Melih2 is omicron-oxidized Ru(18)O2.
field_data.Removed from vacuum: Jazz5 sputtered last year. Melih2 most recently in omicron 19B27.

notes: Jazz5 has, I think, never been tested. It will serve as a standard. 01... O2 control looks good. M34/M32 ratio constant at natural ratio (link1) 02... CO2 control shows way too much M46. I do not understand why there is always all this god damn M46. I have to reduce the electrode first and then go back up to get electrochemical CO2 (interestingly it doesn't start coming while reducing the sample, annoyingly for future extraction experiments on Ir. ----- Melih2 01... absolutely no exchange (link3) 02... absolutely no extraction Gave it 10 minutes at 1.33 V vs RHE with CO.
